story:
January 15, 2026

The Silver Woods breathed tonight. As I crossed the ridge, the frost didn't crunch; it hummed. I found the monolith glowing with a rhythmic, indigo light, its runes shifting like liquid mercury. Something is waking beneath the permafrost, calling out in a language of vibrations. 

I feel its pull even now, a dull thrumming against my ribs that refuses to still. My ink is freezing in the well, and the hearth fire has turned a strange, smokeless violet. My eyelids are heavy, weighted by a magical exhaustion I cannot fight. Whatever shifted in the earth today, it will wait for me in the dreamscape. I am about to sleep!
